        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 6:31PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 16
miles south of Ray, or 23 miles northeast of Watford City, moving
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
White Tail Bay Recreation Area, Tobacco Garden Bay Recreation Area,
Charlson, Lewis And Clark State Park, and White Earth Bay Recreation
Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
